source.name: Impervious Surfaces, San Francisco, CA
source.description: 30 m (~100 ft) grid squares with values representing the percent of ground cover that is impervious, meaning the surface does not allow rainwater to seep into the ground, in San Francisco. Examples include asphalt, cement, and roofing materials.
